1
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:11,460
♪Just To Meet You, you fell for me♪

2
00:00:11,480 --> 00:00:15,460
♪Just to meet me, into my trap you fell♪

3
00:00:15,460 --> 00:00:19,240
♪Wanna try a breathless love?♪

4
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:23,490
♪Every move hits the heart, close and sure♪

5
00:00:23,490 --> 00:00:27,460
♪Just To Meet You, you love my playful charm♪

6
00:00:27,460 --> 00:00:31,480
♪Just to meet me,
my romantic little schemes for you♪

7
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:35,170
♪Wanna play another brand-new game?♪

8
00:00:35,170 --> 00:00:40,360
♪Layer by layer, we close the gap♪

9
00:00:40,380 --> 00:00:47,140
=Just To Meet You=

10
00:00:47,140 --> 00:00:48,820
=Episode 24=
=If Happiness Comes This Way=

11
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:22,600
Doctor.

12
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:23,520
Doctor!

13
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:40,240
Doctor.

14
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,230
How is Lang doing?

15
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:43,840
How is he?

16
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:45,760
His vital signs are stable.

17
00:01:46,150 --> 00:01:47,480
The ECG looks normal.

18
00:01:48,070 --> 00:01:48,910
Young Master,

19
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:50,130
you have

20
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:51,640
made it through.

21
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,640
Thank heavens.

22
00:01:59,150 --> 00:02:00,870
Thanks to our ancestors' blessing.

23
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,480
We still have an heir.

24
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:07,120
Please go ahead with your work.

25
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:09,400
- Okay.
- We'll leave.

26
00:02:12,150 --> 00:02:12,990
You brat,

27
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,120
you scared me to death.

28
00:02:22,870 --> 00:02:23,750
I told you

29
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,590
a long time ago

30
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,150
not to trust

31
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,190
Jiang Niannian.

32
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:30,920
See?

33
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:33,030
She's nothing

34
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:36,470
but a gold-digging fraud.

35
00:02:37,190 --> 00:02:38,280
What are you talking about?

36
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:42,840
Didn't Murong Xue
hurt me releasing the gas?

37
00:02:45,430 --> 00:02:46,270
Where's Niannian?

38
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:47,840
That woman

39
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:51,000
stabbed you at the wedding,

40
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,310
and she took her own life in fear.

41
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:58,630
No way.

42
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:00,360
Impossible.

43
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:02,960
We were just together.

44
00:03:04,590 --> 00:03:05,520
It was Murong Xue

45
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:08,590
who was behind all this.

46
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,120
You brat.

47
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:12,870
Half a month in coma

48
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,400
scrambled your brain?

49
00:03:18,150 --> 00:03:18,990
Half a month?

50
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:31,470
Jiang Niannian...

51
00:03:35,710 --> 00:03:36,870
How did she die?

52
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:40,680
Actually,

53
00:03:41,470 --> 00:03:42,310
she didn't

54
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,630
commit any real crime.

55
00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:47,150
Last week,

56
00:03:47,630 --> 00:03:48,870
after she came to see you,

57
00:03:49,590 --> 00:03:50,470
she disappeared.

58
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,590
Yesterday, the police

59
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,400
found it on the surveillance

60
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:57,680
she jumped into the sea.

61
00:04:00,630 --> 00:04:01,470
Jump...

62
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,200
Jump into the sea?

63
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,520
No way.

64
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:27,230
No... No way.

65
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:34,300
(Nurse Station)

66
00:04:34,310 --> 00:04:35,150
Where's Zheng Lu?

67
00:04:36,270 --> 00:04:37,110
Director Ye.

68
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:39,160
Dr. Zheng passed away

69
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,070
in a car accident four months ago.

70
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,840
Then...
What about Jiang Niannian?

71
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,080
Her body...

72
00:04:50,510 --> 00:04:53,510
Ms. Jiang's body hasn't been found yet.

73
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,190
It's the rainy season now.

74
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:57,120
It likely drifted downstream.

75
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:17,000
Was that so-called second life

76
00:05:18,270 --> 00:05:21,310
just a dying dream?

77
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,310
Or was this

78
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:29,390
the price of ending the cycle?

79
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:44,040
I had such a long dream.

80
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:47,440
In it,

81
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:50,480
I met Jiang Niannian again.

82
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:52,680
I got close to her.

83
00:05:53,870 --> 00:05:55,160
I let her deceive me.

84
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:58,000
I swore

85
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:01,360
I'd never trust her again.

86
00:06:03,390 --> 00:06:05,680
But I still fell for her again.

87
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,920
We fought in the morning light,

88
00:06:10,860 --> 00:06:12,260
and held each other in the downpour.

89
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,190
We made a promise

90
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:17,750
we'd never be apart again

91
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,600
and we'd build a beautiful future.

92
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:25,780
♪Warm light, softly hazy♪

93
00:06:25,890 --> 00:06:29,580
♪Spilling over your silhouette♪

94
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:33,680
♪Snowflakes gently soothe♪

95
00:06:34,350 --> 00:06:37,960
♪That restless heart♪

96
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:44,850
♪I falling for you, I falling you♪

97
00:06:44,870 --> 00:06:47,830
But I still underestimated
the power of hatred.

98
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:51,000
Murong Xue ruined her,

99
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,430
also me.

100
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:57,290
♪I falling for you, I falling you♪

101
00:06:57,310 --> 00:06:58,950
If there really is a next life,

102
00:07:02,310 --> 00:07:04,680
I hope she and I never meet again.

103
00:07:06,950 --> 00:07:08,750
That would be the best ending.

104
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:31,560
Niannian.

105
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,440
Is that you?

106
00:07:39,630 --> 00:07:40,480
You're alive?

107
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,000
That's really good.

108
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:45,760
You...

109
00:07:45,940 --> 00:07:46,840
Don't come any closer.

110
00:07:49,310 --> 00:07:50,150
Niannian.

111
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:51,550
What are you trying to do?

112
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,630
I don't know you.

113
00:07:57,750 --> 00:07:58,750
I'm Ye Lang.

114
00:07:59,830 --> 00:08:00,830
Don't remember me?

115
00:08:01,950 --> 00:08:03,390
I've never known any Lang.

116
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:06,120
You must have the wrong person.

117
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,640
I'm sorry.

118
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,120
Maybe I got the wrong person.

119
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:05,630
I had a really long dream.

120
00:09:07,030 --> 00:09:07,870
In it,

121
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:10,510
I was with him again.

122
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,120
I lied to him,

123
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:16,920
and left him behind.

124
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,720
I was driven by hatred not even mine,

125
00:09:23,750 --> 00:09:25,200
and was used,

126
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,280
again,

127
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,750
and again, to hurt him.

128
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,510
Only then did I understand

129
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:37,240
I'd already fallen in love with him.

130
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,150
We overcame so many obstacles...

131
00:09:43,350 --> 00:09:46,320
♪Stitched-up lips
tear open a blood-red dusk♪

132
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:48,790
And finally ended up together.

133
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:57,950
♪You return reborn,
seeing through all my cracks♪

134
00:09:58,510 --> 00:10:05,510
♪This tenderness, a trap or a gift?♪

135
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:08,580
♪Still, I'd wager my next life on it♪

136
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:09,440
But a dream

137
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:12,240
is just a dream.

138
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:15,440
One day, you have to wake up.

139
00:10:17,870 --> 00:10:19,080
Maybe

140
00:10:19,670 --> 00:10:21,000
this is the best ending.

141
00:10:23,510 --> 00:10:24,350
In this life,

142
00:10:25,670 --> 00:10:26,600
let's never meet again.

143
00:10:26,610 --> 00:10:31,990
♪Breaking free
from dead vines in the ashes♪

144
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:33,240
At least he's still alive.

145
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:38,360
As for me...

146
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:44,670
♪Freeing me from this half-life prison♪

147
00:10:44,670 --> 00:10:49,510
♪As the bells shatter the past♪

148
00:10:49,630 --> 00:10:50,510
I...

149
00:10:50,510 --> 00:10:54,840
♪Life finds its way again♪

150
00:11:11,060 --> 00:11:18,740
(The End)

151
00:11:35,420 --> 00:11:41,980
♪Stitched-up lips
tear open a blood-red dusk♪

152
00:11:43,820 --> 00:11:50,020
♪You return reborn,
seeing through all my cracks♪

153
00:11:50,580 --> 00:11:57,580
♪This tenderness, a trap or a gift?♪

154
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:00,780
♪Still, I'd wager my next life on it♪

155
00:12:00,780 --> 00:12:05,780
♪Just for a moment to recognize you again♪

156
00:12:05,780 --> 00:12:10,020
♪You are the blazing light in my despair♪

157
00:12:10,540 --> 00:12:14,460
♪Lighting the edges of my frozen wings♪

158
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:18,300
♪I burn myself,
leaping into an illusion of fire♪

159
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:24,060
♪Breaking free
from dead vines in the ashes♪

160
00:12:24,060 --> 00:12:28,380
♪You are the brightest star in the night♪

161
00:12:28,420 --> 00:12:32,220
♪Awakening my dormant fate♪

162
00:12:32,220 --> 00:12:36,740
♪Freeing me from this half-life prison♪

163
00:12:36,740 --> 00:12:41,580
♪As the bells shatter the past♪

164
00:12:41,980 --> 00:12:48,540
♪Life finds its way again♪
